extractive_answers.content: Dynamic Energy Model The dynamic energy model is a resource balancing mechanism of the TRON network, which can dynamically adjust the energy consumption of each contract according to the resource occupancy of the contract, so as to make the allocation of energy resources on the chain more reasonable and prevent excessive concentration of network resources on a few popular contracts.
